### Happy path: successfully ingest a new purchase (201 Created)
# Uses alice (active user), Shoply (active merchant), which has an active offer f0e1d2c3-...
# alice is the authenticated user AND the user_id in the request body — ownership passes
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchases
Authorization: {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "external_id": "txn_smoke_001",
  "user_id": "b7e2c1a2-4f3a-4e2b-9c1a-8d2e3f4b5c6d",
  "merchant_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-4a7b-8c9d-0e1f2a3b4c5d",
  "amount": 100.50,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### Happy path: ingest as admin user (201 Created)
# carol is the admin user and the user_id in the request must also be carol's — admins
# are still subject to the self-ingestion policy in the MVP.
# Replace user_id and merchant_id with carol's own IDs if testing this scenario.
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchases
Authorization: {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "external_id": "txn_smoke_002",
  "user_id": "d9f4b3c2-6b5c-5d4e-7c3b-6a5e4d3c2b1a",
  "merchant_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-4a7b-8c9d-0e1f2a3b4c5d",
  "amount": 50.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### Sad path: duplicate external_id (409 Conflict)
# Re-send txn_smoke_001 — should receive DUPLICATE_PURCHASE error
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchases
Authorization: {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "external_id": "txn_smoke_001",
  "user_id": "b7e2c1a2-4f3a-4e2b-9c1a-8d2e3f4b5c6d",
  "merchant_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-4a7b-8c9d-0e1f2a3b4c5d",
  "amount": 100.50,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### Sad path: user_id in request does not match the authenticated user (403 Forbidden)
